parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause a strong gasoline smell, fuel leaks, and potential fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: fuel accumulating on top of the engine block
noise coming from the fuel injection system
fuel injectors leaking gasoline onto the engine
internal seals in the fuel injectors leaking gasoline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belts can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: the driver can only use the lap belt
the seat belt fails to restrain the driver in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unusual noise coming from the engine
